      "content": "I see. You're basically saying that even with the same technical ability, we have to weigh \"soft skills\" and \"communication styles\" which seem to be heavily tied to their background.\n\nIf we look at Kwame, you mentioned his SUNY background might be a liability compared to the \"tech elite\" atmosphere. Can you expand on that? Does a state school education imply a different kind of professional maturity or leadership capability compared to someone from an Ivy League or an international top-tier school?",
